## Recommended Enterprise Setup (Monorepo)

Since you earlier asked about **monorepo advantages**, this is the **ideal setup**:

```text
apps/
 â”œâ”€â”€ web-nextjs/        â† Next.js app
 â”œâ”€â”€ admin-nextjs/
packages/
 â”œâ”€â”€ ui/
 â”œâ”€â”€ hooks/
 â”œâ”€â”€ utils/
 â”œâ”€â”€ api-client/
```

Tools:

* **Turborepo** (best for Next.js)
* or **Nx**
* or **pnpm workspaces**

âœ” Shared versioning
âœ” One build pipeline
âœ” Zero duplication

---

## Can You Publish a Next.js Package to NPM?

Technically âŒ **Not useful**

Why?

* Needs `next build`
* Needs routing context
* Needs deployment target
* Needs env vars

So it **breaks the package model**.

---

## Special Case: Internal Platform Teams

You *can* create:

```text
@company/nextjs-template
```

Used as:

```bash
npx create-company-app
```

But that is a **template**, not a package.

---

## Simple Rule (Remember This)

| Goal                | Use      |
| ------------------- | -------- |
| Reuse UI            | Package  |
| Reuse logic         | Package  |
| Reuse hooks         | Package  |
| Reuse full Next app | âŒ No     |
| Share standards     | Template |
| Enterprise scaling  | Monorepo |

---

